channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Report: Kansas City Employee at Center of Harrison Butker 'Doxxing' Tweet Gets the FAFO Treatment
'No open debate': Blue state judge removes controversial ballot initiative after backlash over parents' rights
item.description: A proposed amendment to New York's constitution has been blocked by a judge. Opponents of the ballot initiative say it would have allowed state government to take over parents' rights.

item.title: RNC Hits Secret Service Again Over Convention Security
item.description: The Republican National Committee sent another letter to the head of the Secret Service on Thursday, demanding she take "personal and immediate steps" to fix an "unacceptable flaw" in the security plan: the proximity of a protest zone to Fiserv Forum, site of the convention.

item.title: Anchor Spills Beans on Dem Effort to Get Protesters for Trump Rally, Protest Fail Is Incredibly Funny
DOJ's inspector general takes heat for allegedly 'targeting political opponents'
item.description: The Office of Inspector General at the Justice Department is facing allegations of political bias in a Freedom of Information Act request.

item.title: Karoline Leavitt to Newsmax: Trump Draws Crowds 'From All Backgrounds'
item.description: Karoline Leavitt told Newsmax on Thursday night that no matter where former President Donald Trump goes, "he draws massive, enthusiastic crowds of Americans from all backgrounds.

item.title: Senators Rip Biden's Judicial Nominee Over Admitting Trans Male Rapist Into Female Prison
EPA shoots down Alabama coal ash regulation proposal
item.description: The Environmental Protection Agency rejected Thursday a proposal by Alabama to take over coal ash regulation, citing insufficient protections in the state plan.

item.title: Manhattan DA Won't Be Punished for Doc Dump That Delayed Start of Trump Criminal Trial
item.description: Manhattan prosecutors won't be penalized for a last-minute document dump that caused former President Donald Trump's criminal trial to start later than scheduled, a judge ruled Thursday.Judge Juan M. Merchan rejected the defense's request that prosecutors be sanctioned for...

item.title: SHOCKER: Ohio's Mike DeWine Tries to Make Legislature Keep Joe Biden on the Ballot
New York Gov. Kathy Hochul calls Trump supporters ‘clowns’ in her own 'basket of deplorables' moment
item.description: New York Gov. Kathy Hochul called Trump supporters “clowns" on Thursday during a media appearance ahead of the former president’s New York City rally in the Bronx.

item.title: Trump Brings Message of 'Success' to the Bronx
item.description: Speaking to a deep-blue district in a deep-blue state, presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump brought a new wrinkle to his usual campaign rally speech Thursday, briefly eschewing politics to talk about "success."

item.title: Republicans Need to Stay on Target
Trump vows to 'save' deep-blue New York City in massive, historic Bronx rally
item.description: Thousands of people rallied for former President Donald Trump in the Bronx's Crotona Park, one of New York City's deepest-blue areas.

item.title: Trump on Mass Migration: 'They're Building an Army!'
item.description: Speaking to New Yorkers in a rare trip to the deep-blue city and state, presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump issued a stark warning about mass illegal immigration under President Joe Biden destroying "your lifestyle" and "American dream."
